articles.author: Tom Nicholson
articles.title: Liberals lead in Slovakia election, exit poll shows - POLITICO Europe
articles.description: Progressive Slovakia, led by Michal Šimečka, has 23.5 percent of the vote, ahead of former PM Robert Fico’s Smer with 21.9 percent, according to exit poll.
articles.content:
Liberal, Western-oriented Progressive Slovakia was leading Slovakia’s election on Saturday, followed by the leftist-populist Smer opposition party, an exit poll indicated.
